{
    "can-content": {
        "title": "(ㄹ/을) 수 있다/없다,못 (can do,can't do)",
        "content": [
            {
                "title": "When we want to say we can do something, we conjugate korean verbs by removing the verb stem '다' and replacing it with (ㄹ/을)수 있어요. If we can't do something, then we replace '다' with (ㄹ/을)수 없다. If we are unable to do something, we use 못 + Verb.",
                "details": "1. When the verb's last character is a consonant, we replace the stem with '을 수 있어요' if we want to say 'can' or '을 수 없어요' if we want to say 'cannot'. <br/>2. When the verb's last character is a vowel, we append ㄹ to the bottom of the verb and add '수 있어요' if we want to say 'can' or '수 없어요' if we want to say 'cannot'.<br/>3. If we want to say we are unable to do something (this is slightly different than cannot), we use the word '못' + Verb, or Verb + '지 못하다'."
            }
        ],
        "button": "<p><a href='#!/lesson/level2/frequency' class='btn btn-primary btn-prev btn-lg' role='button'>Previous lesson</a><a href='#!/lesson/level2/should' class='btn btn-primary btn-next btn-lg' role='button'>Ok, next lesson</a></p>"
    },
